---
description: Prevent accidental inclusion of secrets and credentials in AI prompts
alwaysApply: true
---

Never include the following in AI prompts or generated code without explicit developer approval:

- API keys, access tokens, or authentication credentials
- Private keys or certificates
- Database connection strings with embedded passwords
- Environment variable values that contain secrets
- AWS access keys (AKIA prefix)
- GitHub personal access tokens (ghp_ prefix)
- Slack tokens (xoxb-, xoxp- prefix)
- JWT tokens (eyJ prefix with three dot-separated segments)

If code being reviewed or generated contains these patterns, suggest using environment variables or secret management tools instead.

When asked to work with configuration files (.env, config.yaml, secrets.json), remind the developer that file contents will be sent to the AI model provider.
